{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"It began with one question:"},{"time":5222,"text":"If Africa was a bar, what would\nyour country be drinking or doing?"},{"time":11680,"text":"I kicked it off with a guess\nabout South Africa,"},{"time":14480,"text":"which wasn't exactly\naccording to the rules"},{"time":16560,"text":"because South Africa's not my country."},{"time":19640,"text":"But alluding to the country's\ncontinual attempts"},{"time":22920,"text":"to build a postracial society"},{"time":25280,"text":"after being ravaged\nfor decades by apartheid,"},{"time":28600,"text":"I tweeted, #ifafricawasabar South Africa\nwould be drinking all kinds of alcohol"},{"time":34960,"text":"and begging them\nto get along in its stomach."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38960,"text":"And then I waited."},{"time":40680,"text":"And then I had that funny feeling\nwhere I wondered if I crossed the line."},{"time":44160,"text":"So, I sent out a few other tweets\nabout my own country"},{"time":47360,"text":"and a few other African countries\nI'm familiar with."},{"time":50400,"text":"And then I waited again,"},{"time":51680,"text":"but this time"},{"time":53080,"text":"I read through almost every tweet\nI had ever tweeted"},{"time":56520,"text":"to convince myself,"},{"time":58280,"text":"no, to remind myself that I'm really funny"},{"time":62400,"text":"and that if nobody gets it, that's fine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66960,"text":"But luckily,"},{"time":68200,"text":"I didn't have to do that for very long."},{"time":70440,"text":"Very soon, people were participating."},{"time":74280,"text":"In fact, by the end of that week in July,"},{"time":77560,"text":"the hashtag #ifafricawasabar"},{"time":80120,"text":"would have garnered around 60,000 tweets,"},{"time":83840,"text":"lit up the continent"},{"time":85520,"text":"and made its way to publications\nall over the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":89240,"text":"People were using the hashtag\nto do many different things."},{"time":93280,"text":"To poke fun at their stereotypes:"},{"time":95480,"text":"[#IfAfricaWasABar\nNigeria would be outside explaining"},{"time":98120,"text":"that he will pay the entrance fee,"},{"time":99920,"text":"all he needs is\nthe bouncer's account details.]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":102360,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":103600,"text":"To criticize government spending:"},{"time":106000,"text":"[#ifafricawasabar South Africa would be\nordering bottles it can't pronounce"},{"time":109600,"text":"running a tab it won't be able to pay]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":111480,"text":"To make light of geopolitical tensions:"},{"time":114080,"text":"[#IfAfricaWasABar\nSouth Sudan would be the new guy"},{"time":116480,"text":"with serious anger management issues.]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":118720,"text":"To remind us that even in Africa"},{"time":120600,"text":"there are some countries\nwe don't know exist:"},{"time":123080,"text":"[#IfAfricaWasABar\nLesotho would be that person"},{"time":125480,"text":"who nobody really knows\nbut is always in the pictures.]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":128520,"text":"And also to make fun of the countries\nthat don't think that they're in Africa:"},{"time":132800,"text":"[#IfAfricaWasABar Egypt, Libya,\nTunisia, Algeria and Morocco"},{"time":135840,"text":"be like \"What the hell\nare we doing here?!!\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":138080,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":140000,"text":"And to note the countries\nthat had made a big turnaround:"},{"time":144120,"text":"[#ifAfricawasabar\nRwanda would be that girl"},{"time":146160,"text":"that comes with no money and no transport\nbut leaves drunk, happy and rich]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":149800,"text":"But most importantly,"},{"time":152360,"text":"people were using the hashtag to connect."},{"time":155640,"text":"People were connecting\nover their Africanness."},{"time":159000,"text":"So for one week in July,"},{"time":161320,"text":"Twitter became a real African bar."},{"time":165600,"text":"And I was really thrilled,"},{"time":167000,"text":"mainly because I realized\nthat Pan-Africanism could work,"},{"time":172200,"text":"that we had before us,\nbetween us, at our fingertips"},{"time":177520,"text":"a platform that just needed a small spark"},{"time":181000,"text":"to light in us a hunger for each other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":185120,"text":"My name is Siyanda Mohutsiwa,"},{"time":187320,"text":"I'm 22 years old"},{"time":189080,"text":"and I am Pan-Africanist by birth."},{"time":192160,"text":"Now, I say I'm Pan-Africanist by birth"},{"time":194680,"text":"because my parents are\nfrom two different African countries."},{"time":198080,"text":"My father's from a country\ncalled Botswana in southern Africa."},{"time":201840,"text":"It's only slightly bigger than Germany."},{"time":204880,"text":"This year we celebrate\nour 50th year of stable democracy."},{"time":209000,"text":"And it has some very progressive\nsocial policies."},{"time":212600,"text":"My mother's country\nis the Kingdom of Swaziland."},{"time":216640,"text":"It's a very, very small country,\nalso in southern Africa."},{"time":219880,"text":"It is Africa's last complete monarchy."},{"time":223520,"text":"So it's been ruled by a king\nand a royal family"},{"time":226360,"text":"in line with their tradition,"},{"time":227800,"text":"for a very long time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229880,"text":"On paper, these countries\nseem very different."},{"time":232880,"text":"And when I was a kid,\nI could see the difference."},{"time":236440,"text":"It rained a lot in one country,\nit didn't rain quite as much in the other."},{"time":240920,"text":"But outside of that,\nI didn't really realize"},{"time":243320,"text":"why it mattered that my parents\nwere from two different places."},{"time":247720,"text":"But it would go on\nto have a very peculiar effect on me."},{"time":251920,"text":"You see, I was born in one country"},{"time":254680,"text":"and raised in the other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256760,"text":"When we moved to Botswana,"},{"time":258680,"text":"I was a toddler who spoke fluent SiSwati"},{"time":261640,"text":"and nothing else."},{"time":263240,"text":"So I was being introduced to my new home,"},{"time":265960,"text":"my new cultural identity,"},{"time":268240,"text":"as a complete outsider,"},{"time":270280,"text":"incapable of comprehending\nanything that was being said to me"},{"time":274560,"text":"by the family and country whose traditions\nI was meant to move forward."},{"time":279000,"text":"But very soon, I would shed SiSwati."},{"time":283240,"text":"And when I would go back to Swaziland,"},{"time":285520,"text":"I would be constantly confronted\nby how very non-Swazi I was becoming."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290640,"text":"Add to that my entry\ninto Africa's private school system,"},{"time":294520,"text":"whose entire purpose\nis to beat the Africanness out of you,"},{"time":298840,"text":"and I would have\na very peculiar adolescence."},{"time":302240,"text":"But I think that my interest\nin ideas of identity was born here,"},{"time":308120,"text":"in the strange intersection\nof belonging to two places at once"},{"time":312400,"text":"but not really belonging\nto either one very well"},{"time":315520,"text":"and belonging to this vast space\nin between and around simultaneously."},{"time":321400,"text":"I became obsessed with the idea\nof a shared African identity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":328560,"text":"Since then, I have continued\nto read about politics"},{"time":331360,"text":"and geography and identity\nand what all those things mean."},{"time":334800,"text":"I've also held on to a deep curiosity\nabout African philosophies."},{"time":339560,"text":"When I began to read,"},{"time":340840,"text":"I gravitated towards the works\nof black intellectuals"},{"time":344280,"text":"like Steve Biko and Frantz Fanon,"},{"time":346760,"text":"who tackled complex ideas"},{"time":348600,"text":"like decolonization\nand black consciousness."},{"time":351680,"text":"And when I thought, at 14,\nthat I had digested these grand ideas,"},{"time":355920,"text":"I moved on to the speeches\nof iconic African statesmen"},{"time":360000,"text":"like Burkina Faso's Thomas Sankara"},{"time":363040,"text":"and Congo's Patrice Lumumba."},{"time":365480,"text":"I read every piece of African fiction\nthat I could get my hands on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":369880,"text":"So when Twitter came,"},{"time":371560,"text":"I hopped on with the enthusiasm\nof a teenage girl"},{"time":375760,"text":"whose friends are super, super bored\nof hearing about all this random stuff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":382280,"text":"The year was 2011"},{"time":383640,"text":"and all over southern Africa\nand the whole continent,"},{"time":386720,"text":"affordable data packages\nfor smartphones and Internet surfing"},{"time":390640,"text":"became much easier to get."},{"time":393480,"text":"So my generation, we were sending\nmessages to each other on this platform"},{"time":398960,"text":"that just needed 140 characters\nand a little bit of creativity."},{"time":403440,"text":"On long commutes to work,"},{"time":405880,"text":"in lectures that some of us\nshould have been paying attention to,"},{"time":409360,"text":"on our lunch breaks,"},{"time":410960,"text":"we would communicate as much as we could"},{"time":413000,"text":"about the everyday realities\nof being young and African."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416880,"text":"But of course, this luxury\nwas not available to everybody."},{"time":420400,"text":"So this meant that if you were\na teenage girl in Botswana"},{"time":424120,"text":"and you wanted\nto have fun on the Internet,"},{"time":426200,"text":"one, you had to tweet in English."},{"time":428880,"text":"Two, you had to follow more than just\nthe three other people you knew online."},{"time":433680,"text":"You had to follow South Africans,\nZimbabweans, Ghanaians, Nigerians."},{"time":438760,"text":"And suddenly, your whole world opened up."},{"time":441560,"text":"And my whole world did open up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":443920,"text":"I followed vibrant Africans\nwho were travelling around the continent,"},{"time":447760,"text":"taking pictures of themselves"},{"time":449240,"text":"and posting them\nunder the hashtag #myafrica."},{"time":452360,"text":"Because at that time,"},{"time":453840,"text":"if you were to search Africa\non Twitter or on Google"},{"time":456920,"text":"or any kind of social media,"},{"time":459200,"text":"you would think that the entire continent\nwas just pictures of animals"},{"time":463000,"text":"and white guys drinking cocktails\nin hotel resorts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":466520,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":468800,"text":"But Africans were using this platform"},{"time":471360,"text":"to take some kind of ownership\nof the tourism sectors."},{"time":475440,"text":"It was Africans taking selfies\non the beaches of Nigeria."},{"time":479480,"text":"It was Africans\nin cocktail bars in Nairobi."}]},{"cues":[{"time":483040,"text":"And these were the same Africans\nthat I began to meet"},{"time":485541,"text":"in my own travels around the continent."},{"time":488000,"text":"We would discuss African literature,\npolitics, economic policy."},{"time":493000,"text":"But almost invariably, every single time,"},{"time":497160,"text":"we would end up discussing Twitter."},{"time":500160,"text":"And that's when I realized what this was."},{"time":503120,"text":"We were standing in the middle\nof something amazing,"},{"time":506440,"text":"because for the first time ever"},{"time":508760,"text":"young Africans could discuss\nthe future of our continent in real time,"},{"time":513840,"text":"without the restriction of borders,\nfinances and watchful governments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":518720,"text":"Because the little known truth is"},{"time":520679,"text":"many Africans know a lot less\nabout other African countries"},{"time":524560,"text":"than some Westerners\nmight know about Africa as a whole."},{"time":528160,"text":"This is by accident,"},{"time":529760,"text":"but sometimes, it's by design."},{"time":531920,"text":"For example, in apartheid South Africa,"},{"time":534880,"text":"black South Africans\nwere constantly being bombarded"},{"time":538400,"text":"with this message that any country\nruled by black people"},{"time":541520,"text":"was destined for failure."},{"time":543520,"text":"And this was done to convince them"},{"time":546080,"text":"that they were much better off\nunder crushing white rule"},{"time":549760,"text":"than they were living\nin a black and free nation."},{"time":553640,"text":"Add to that Africa's colonial,\narchaic education system,"},{"time":558880,"text":"which has been unthinkingly\ncarried over from the 1920s --"},{"time":562880,"text":"and at the age of 15,\nI could name all the various causes"},{"time":567200,"text":"of the wars that had happened\nin Europe in the past 200 years,"},{"time":571280,"text":"but I couldn't name the president\nof my neighboring country."},{"time":574640,"text":"And to me, this doesn't make any sense"},{"time":577520,"text":"because whether we like it or not,"},{"time":579560,"text":"the fates of African people\nare deeply intertwined."}]},{"cues":[{"time":583680,"text":"When disaster hits, when turmoil hits,"},{"time":587200,"text":"we share the consequences."},{"time":589360,"text":"When Burundians flee political turmoil,"},{"time":592360,"text":"they go to us,"},{"time":593720,"text":"to other African countries."},{"time":595760,"text":"Africa has six of the world's\nlargest refugee centers."},{"time":600320,"text":"What was once a Burundian problem"},{"time":603000,"text":"becomes an African problem."},{"time":605040,"text":"So to me, there are no Sudanese problems"},{"time":608640,"text":"or South African problems\nor Kenyan problems,"},{"time":611080,"text":"only African problems"},{"time":612680,"text":"because eventually, we share the turmoil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":615600,"text":"So if we share the problems,"},{"time":617360,"text":"why aren't we doing a better job\nof sharing the successes?"},{"time":621200,"text":"How can we do that?"},{"time":622440,"text":"Well, in the long term,"},{"time":623720,"text":"we can shoot towards\nincreasing inter-African trade,"},{"time":626600,"text":"removing borders\nand putting pressure on leaders"},{"time":629160,"text":"to fulfill regional agreements\nthey've already signed."},{"time":633200,"text":"But I think that the biggest way\nfor Africa to share its successes"},{"time":638360,"text":"is to foster something\nI like to call social Pan-Africanism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":643320,"text":"Now, political Pan-Africanism\nalready exists,"},{"time":646200,"text":"so I'm not inventing anything\ntotally new here."},{"time":649360,"text":"But political Pan-Africanism"},{"time":650960,"text":"is usually the African unity\nof the political elite."},{"time":654520,"text":"And who does that benefit?"},{"time":655880,"text":"Well, African leaders, almost exclusively."},{"time":659280,"text":"No, what I'm talking about"},{"time":662200,"text":"is the Pan-Africanism\nof the ordinary African."},{"time":665840,"text":"Young Africans like me,"},{"time":667920,"text":"we are bursting with creative energy,"},{"time":670920,"text":"with innovative ideas."},{"time":673440,"text":"But with bad governance\nand shaky institutions,"},{"time":676840,"text":"all of this potential could go to waste."},{"time":679520,"text":"On a continent where more\nthan a handful of leaders"},{"time":682080,"text":"have been in power longer"},{"time":683960,"text":"than the majority\nof the populations has been alive,"},{"time":688360,"text":"we are in desperate need of something new,"},{"time":691760,"text":"something that works."},{"time":694000,"text":"And I think that thing\nis social Pan-Africanism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":699560,"text":"My dream is that young Africans"},{"time":702720,"text":"stop allowing borders and circumstance\nto suffocate our innovation."},{"time":708280,"text":"My dream is that when a young African\ncomes up with something brilliant,"},{"time":712640,"text":"they don't say, \"Well,\nthis wouldn't work in my country,\""},{"time":716080,"text":"and then give up."},{"time":717520,"text":"My dream is that young Africans\nbegin to realize"},{"time":721200,"text":"that the entire continent\nis our canvas, is our home."},{"time":726920,"text":"Using the Internet,\nwe can begin to think collaboratively,"},{"time":731280,"text":"we can begin to innovate together."},{"time":733880,"text":"In Africa, we say,\n\"If you want to go fast, you go alone,"},{"time":737480,"text":"but if you want to go far,\nyou go together.\""},{"time":740360,"text":"And I believe that social Pan-Africanism\nis how we can go far together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":747480,"text":"And this is already happening."},{"time":749520,"text":"Access to these online networks\nhas given young Africans"},{"time":752520,"text":"something we've always\nhad to violently take: a voice."},{"time":756920,"text":"We now have a platform."},{"time":758840,"text":"Before now, if you wanted\nto hear from the youth in Africa,"},{"time":762800,"text":"you waited for the 65-year-old\nminister of youth --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":766560,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":767880,"text":"to wake up in the morning,"},{"time":769960,"text":"take his heartburn medication"},{"time":773360,"text":"and then tell you the plans\nhe has for your generation"},{"time":776280,"text":"in 20 years time."},{"time":778400,"text":"Before now, if you wanted to be heard\nby your possibly tyrannical government,"},{"time":784360,"text":"you were pushed to protest,\nsuffer the consequences"},{"time":787760,"text":"and have your fingers crossed"},{"time":789440,"text":"that some Western paper somewhere\nmight make someone care."},{"time":793560,"text":"But now we have opportunities\nto back each other up"},{"time":796400,"text":"in ways we never could before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":798640,"text":"We support South African students"},{"time":800400,"text":"who are marching against\nridiculously high tertiary fees."},{"time":804040,"text":"We support Zimbabwean women\nwho are marching to parliament."},{"time":807400,"text":"We support Angolan journalists\nwho are being illegally detained."},{"time":811560,"text":"For the first time ever,"},{"time":813720,"text":"African pain and African aspiration"},{"time":818200,"text":"has the ability to be witnessed"},{"time":821520,"text":"by those who can empathize\nwith it the most:"},{"time":825160,"text":"other Africans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":826920,"text":"I believe that with\na social Pan-Africanist thinking"},{"time":830880,"text":"and using the Internet as a tool,"},{"time":833920,"text":"we can begin to rescue each other,"},{"time":836800,"text":"and ultimately, to rescue ourselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":840400,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":841640,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}